OL,6,FBut amid straitened public finances,
OL,7,Fpoliticians on both sides have shied
OL,8,Faway from commitments to payouts, with
OL,9,Fneither Labour nor the Conservatives
OL,10,Fsaying whether they would compensate
OL,11,Fthose affected.
OL,13,FThe PHSO suggested compensation could
OL,14,Fcost between #3.5 billion and #10.5
OL,15,Fbillion, although campaigners are
OL,16,Fpushing for a higher figure.
